The conditions are expected to worsen as the boats head into the open  Atlantic Ocean, with the wind predicted to shift to the northeast, producing  large dangerous waves.
"If anyone pushes the boat too hard they will definitely break something,"  Smith said prior to the start.
While Yamaha's lead over Intrum Justicia has been compared to a 35-point  lead in the final quarter of an American football match, Field said he would  not be conservative in the final leg.
"We will race as though we have no time in the bank; we are going out to  win it," he said, adding: "It's easy to lose a 10-hour lead."
